Experts at NHS England decided to add it to the list of approved medicines after requests for access from oncologists and following review of the positive trial results.

Professor Peter Clark, Chair of the Chemotherapy CRG, said ‘This new addition to the list demonstrates NHS England’s commitment to achieving maximum benefit to patients from the £200 million Cancer Drugs Fund.

‘The process of updating the list is led by cancer specialists, and should ensure that patients benefit quickly when new drugs become available that are backed by good evidence from trial data.’ 

It is thought 500 women every year could benefit from the drug, which is routinely available on the NHS before any other country in the world.

